article.headline: Hampton 73, Norfolk State 63
article.story: HAMPTON, Va. (AP) -- Jeff Granger scored 19 points and Devin Green had 16 points and 15 rebounds Tuesday night, leading Hampton to a 73-63 victory against Norfolk State. The Pirates (2-7) led 40-25 at halftime and limited the Spartans to 28 percent shooting in the second half and just 28.6 percent for the game on 14-for-49. Norfolk State (1-5), which went the last 4:44 without a field goal, was led by Derrick Smith with 18 points and 10 rebounds and Chakowby Hicks with 17 points. Hampton had 14 field goals by halftime, matching what the Spartans managed for the entire game. The Pirates also turned 13 turnovers by Norfolk State in 24 points and stayed in fron by making 17 of 21 second-half free-throw attempts. Rodney Hughes and Donald Didlake each added 10 points for Hampton.
